FBIS4-47913 "drafr087_a_94001" FBIS-AFR-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Burundi Interior Minister Leonard Nyangoma Resigns Interior Minister Leonard Nyangoma Resigns LD0405185894 Paris Radio France International in French 1830 GMT 4 May 94 LD0405185894 Paris Radio France International French BFN [Text] In Burundi Leonard Nyangoma, minister of the interior and security, has resigned. This has just been announced this evening by Mr. Kanyenkiko, the prime minister. The minister of the interior has been abroad for several weeks. He was accused by the Burundi Armed Forces of being behind the armed gangs they have been clashing with for several weeks in the northern outskirts of Bujumbura.
